tage 3 [[Volta a la Comunitat Valenciana]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Vuelta a Arag\u00f3n]]\n;1996\n: 1st [[Paris\u2013Tours]]\n: [[1996 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n::1st Stages 2, 8, 9 & 16\n: [[Vuelta a Burgos]]\n::1st Stages 1 & 5\n: 1st Stage 5 [[Danmark Rundt]]\n;1997\n: [[1997 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n::1st Stages 4 & 21\n: Gran Premio Jornal de Noticias\n::1st Stages 1 & 2\n: [[Volta ao Alentejo]]\n::1st Stages 1 & 4\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Danmark Rundt]]\n: 1st Stage 3 [[Giro di Puglia]]\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Giro di Sardegna]]\n;1998\n: 1st Giro dell'Etna\n: 1st Stage 3 [[1998 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n: 1st Stage 3a [[Rheinland-Pfalz Rundfahrt]]\n: 1st Stage 5a [[Setmana Catalana de Ciclisme]]\n: 1st Stage 5 [[Tour M\u00e9diterran\u00e9en]]\n;1999\n: 1st Stage 1 [[Four Days of Dunkirk]]\n: 1st Stage 5 [[Settimana Lombarda]]\n;2001\n: [[Tour of Rhodes]]\n::1st Stages 1 & 2 \n: 1st Stage 5 [[Postgirot Open]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{trapfriis|italy.Minali.htm}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Minali, Nicola}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Verona]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Italian Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:Italian Giro d'Italia stage winners]]\n[[Category:Italian Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:Tour de France Champs Elys\u00e9es stage winners]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Veneto]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-1960s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicola_Minali"}
{"title_page": "2020 United States Senate election in Kentucky", "text_new": "{{For|related races|2020 United States Senate elections}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{short description|Election to elect a United States Senator from Kentucky in 2020}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 2020 United States Senate election in Kentucky\n| country            = Kentucky\n| type               = presidential\n| ongoing            = yes\n| previous_election  = 2014 United States Senate election in Kentucky\n| previous_year      = 2014\n| next_election      = 2026 United States Senate election in Kentucky\n| next_year          = 2026\n| election_date      = November 3, 2020\n| image1             =\n| nominee1           =\n| party1             = Republican Party (United States)\n| popular_vote1      =\n| percentage1        =\n| image2             =\n| nominee2           =\n| party2             = Democratic Party (United States)\n| popular_vote2      =\n| percentage2        =\n| map_image          =\n| map_size           =\n| map_caption        = County results\n| title              = U.S. Senator\n| before_election    = [[Mitch McConnell]]\n| before_party       = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election     =\n| after_party        =\n}}\n{{ElectionsKY}}\n\nThe '''2020 United States Senate election in Kentucky''' will be held on November 3, 2020, to elect a member of the [[United States Senate]] to represent the [[Kentucky|Commonwealth of Kentucky]], concurrently with the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]], as well as [[2020 United States Senate elections|other elections]] to the U.S. Senate and [[2020 United States House of Representatives elections|elections]] to the [[United States House of Representatives]] and various [[2020 United States elections|state and local elections]].\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n* Nicholas Alsager<ref name=\"wdrb\"/> \n* Wendell K. Crow, businessman and entrepreneur<ref name=\"wdrb\">https://www.wdrb.com/news/senate-majority-leader-mitch-mcconnell-just-got-two-more-primary/article_18e3efd2-2201-11ea-b2fc-a74f0ffbe713.html</ref>\n* Paul John Frangedakis, chiropractor<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* Louis Grider, truck driver<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* Neren James<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* Kenneth Lowndes<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* [[Mitch McConnell]], incumbent U.S. Senator<ref>[http://www.miamiherald.com/news/politics-government/article213094359.html/ Mitch McConnell to Kentucky Gov. Bevin: Stay home and run for re-election]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/1c57404aaea9427fba5478dd61f5a801|title=McConnell announces re-elect campaign at Fancy Farm picnic|work=Associated Press|first=Adam|last=Beam|date=August 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Wesley Morgan (politician)|Wesley Morgan]], former state representative<ref name=\"Morgan\">{{cite news |last1=Brammer |first1=Jack |title=Former Kentucky lawmaker challenging Mitch McConnell in GOP primary for U.S. Senate |url=https://www.kentucky.com/news/politics-government/article230935263.html |accessdate=May 31, 2019 |work=Lexington Herald Leader |date=May 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Declined====\n* [[Matt Bevin]], former [[Governor of Kentucky]] (endorsed McConnell)<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Cohen|first=Zach C.|user=Zachary_Cohen|number=1103325058007789569|title=Lil' news in the kicker here: #KYgov @MattBevin, McConnell's 2014 primary challenger, said he will \u201cof course\u201d support McConnell\u2019s #KYsen reelection in 2020.\ud83d\udd12http://njour.nl/s/677069|date=March 6, 2019|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jenean Hampton]], former [[Lieutenant Governor of Kentucky]] {{Citation needed|date=December 2019}}\n\n===Endorsements===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Mitch McConnell\n| list =\n;Federal officials\n* [[Donald Trump]], 45th President of the United States<ref>{{cite tweet|user=realDonaldTrump|number=1148747083219984384|title=Democrats are coming after our great Kentucky S